Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.90,0:00:07.90,Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(349,414)\fade(255,0,255,0,1665,4940,6060)}Hunged seal and locked gold
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.45,0:00:17.76,Thinking,Narrator,0,0,0,,After Cáo Cāo accepted Guān Yǔ's three terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:19.85,Thinking,Narrator,0,0,0,,Guān Yǔ often missed Liú Bèi on one side
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.85,0:00:23.16,Thinking,Narrator,0,0,0,,and took care of Ladies Gān and Mí on the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.32,0:00:26.78,Thinking,Narrator,0,0,0,,whilst following Cáo Cāo to Xǔdū (Xǔchāng).
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.52,0:00:32.60,Thinking,Narrator,0,0,0,,Liú Bèi having lost Xiaopei, the Xu-Province, and Xiapi in quick succession,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.70,0:00:35.08,Thinking,Narrator,0,0,0,,and had no choice but to join with Yuán Shào.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.76,0:00:40.83,Thinking,Narrator,0,0,0,,Zhāng Fēi broke out of a heavy siege and left towards Mount Mángdàng.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.73,0:00:48.65,Default,GuanYu,0,0,0,,Sisters-in-law, you must be exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.65,0:00:52.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,However, we still need to travel tomorrow, so please rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.98,0:00:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle, you must be tired as well, please rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.90,0:01:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,General, please rest. We will take our leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.60,0:01:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead me to the living quarters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.52,0:01:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you moving?\NThe living quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.14,0:01:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,General, the soldiers take rest in the streets
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.74,0:01:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,while sir general and the two mistresses has had it hard on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.05,0:01:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Under Chancellor’s orders, this room \Nis arranged just for you and the two mistresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.36,0:01:37.06,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(107.537,341.333)}Guān Yǔ\NStyled: Yúncháng
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.32,0:01:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Just this room? \NTo house me and the two mistresses?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:42.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,General, this one doesn’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.15,0:01:47.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,These are all under Chancellor's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Obscene!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.41,0:02:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he wish to ruin my name, \Nupheave the bond between lord and vassal?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.18,0:02:43.38,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(597.799,329.333)}Cáo Cāo\NStyled: Mèngdé
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.29,0:02:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched the night at thy orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:52.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,But General Guān has been outside all night under candlelight. He simply won't sway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.38,0:03:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You must serve the mistresses well!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.25,0:03:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor Cáo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed your cloaks are well-worn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.92,0:03:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let this fine silk be your new war cloak, \Nmade just for your size!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The distance to {\i1}Xǔdū{\i0} (Xǔchāng) is significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.10,0:03:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For all that could trouble on the road,\N I hope you will forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.48,0:04:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, come and take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It fits well, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.72,0:04:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yúnchǎng, why be so modest?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.16,0:04:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,441.637)}It is not due to modesty, this old robe was from the Imperial Uncle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,441.637)}my brother's gift for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.54,0:05:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,441.637)}I couldn't wear what Chancellor has given, and forgotten my elder brother's grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.44,0:05:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,441.637)}So I shall wear the old robe over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,441.637)}You are indeed a man of princible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.92,0:05:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.98,0:05:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yúnchǎng, why is your mount so feeble?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.32,0:05:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My body is heavy and the horse cannot bear it, thus he is thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.17,0:05:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yúnchǎng, do you recognize this horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.65,0:05:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be... Lǚ Bù's horse, {\i1}the Red Hare?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, why not ride it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:36.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Chancellor, this is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.46,0:06:39.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If Guān Yǔ gets this horse, he might escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yúnchǎng would not be so dishonorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.14,0:06:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Liú Bèi's two wives are still in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.28,0:06:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.41,0:07:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.39,0:07:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:26.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I gave you a silk cloak, and you didn't kneel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.96,0:07:31.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yet I give you a horse, \Nand you kneel in reverence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.41,0:07:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you value beasts over men?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, this horse can travel\N thousands of lǐ in one day, and you grant it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.00,0:07:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I learn of my elder brother's whereabouts, I can be with him in that one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:08:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You receive this much generosity, yet you still ponder leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.04,0:08:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, I'm grateful for your kindness!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,However, though I am here, my heart yearns for Imperial Uncle Liú!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.67,0:08:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother speaks in err.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A man should weigh the value of all matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:33.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Lord Xuándé's grace, may hardly compare to our Chancellor's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.09,0:08:36.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why do you wish to leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.95,0:08:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I do know the Chancellor has given me much,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but I also received the imperial \Nuncle's love. We swore to die together!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.69,0:08:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not betray that oath!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.77,0:09:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, I cannot remain here forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I will repay you, sire, then will I depart!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.75,0:09:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But if Xuándé has left the world, where would you turn to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.38,0:09:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I will follow him in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.36,0:09:35.80,Thinking,,0,0,0,,This man never forgot his roots. \NYúnchǎng is a righteous man in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Generals, we shall march to Xǔdū!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.05,0:09:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Move away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.62,0:09:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Return Yúnchǎng to his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.78,0:10:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,After you, Xuándé.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.96,0:10:16.22,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(602.441,324)}Yuán Shào\NStyled: Běnchū
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.14,0:10:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuándé, your face tells me something is amiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.92,0:10:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuándé,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know why you are always aggrieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no news of my two brothers, and my family are in the hands of that traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.00,0:10:47.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Above, I cannot repay the nation. \NBelow, I cannot repay my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:51.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,How could anyone stay still and not be aggrieved?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long wanted to breach into Xǔdū. \NNow we have a rising army to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.09,0:11:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo has deceived his lord treacherously. \NIf my Lord were to resist him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this will win over and unite the heroes all across the realm!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.65,0:11:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.24,0:11:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when Cáo Cāo attacked Xú Province, Xǔdū \Nwas open, but Your Lordship did not advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.10,0:11:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Xú Province has been conquered! \NThe army of Cáo cannot be underestimated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be better to maintain our position and await for a chance to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.80,0:11:53.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,My Lord, Cáo Cāo is deceitful,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.16,0:11:58.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If we don't act now, I fear you will lose your ground amidst the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.51,0:12:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuándé's words are true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.18,0:12:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sire, Liú Bèi cannot be trusted!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.45,0:12:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.89,0:12:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You belittle our strength with your tongue, do you deem me to fail?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:17.14,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,540,1900,2380)\pos(591.472,336)}Tián Fēng\NStyled: Yuánhào
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.98,0:12:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord! To ignore our words is to doom our men!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.68,0:12:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The gall!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Guards, drag him out! Off with his head!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.70,0:12:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sire, don't pay our loyalty with your regret!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord, Tián Yuánhào has affronted your esteem. While this is indeed contemptible,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,however, to kill your own before mobilizing any troops, would only harm the men's morale.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.83,0:12:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope Sire will consider this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.97,0:13:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Imprison Tián Fēng. He will remain there until the end of the campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord! Sire! Don't pay our loyalty with your regret!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord! My Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.47,0:13:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Assign Yán Liáng as vanguard! \NHe shall attack Báimǎ!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.72,0:13:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The main army shall follow me \Nas scheduled to advance to Líyáng!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.13,0:13:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sòng Xiàn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:26.00,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(429.841,234.286)}	Bómǎ
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.95,0:13:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.58,0:13:53.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I've long heard you were \Na mighty warrior-general under Lǚ Bù.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.80,0:13:56.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Would you honor us by taking on Yán Liáng?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.55,0:14:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, watch me seize Yán Liáng's head!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Witness my strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.54,0:14:22.64,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(124.202,344.286)}Yán Liáng
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.22,0:14:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He truly is a valiant fighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, Yán Liáng killed my friend! \NI am willing to risk my life to avenge him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.43,0:14:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yán Liáng! Today, I will send you to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who will challenge him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.00,0:15:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.54,0:15:11.06,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,540,1900,2380)\pos(110.465,361.143)}Xú Huǎng\N Styled Gōngmíng
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.82,0:15:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord! My Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.44,0:15:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound the bells!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.38,0:16:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, I know one man able to match Yán Liáng.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.72,0:16:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.06,0:16:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Guān Yúncháng.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But before, he stated he wouldn't leave until he repays us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.83,0:16:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He would leave after he repays us. \NI can't let him join the fray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If Liú Bèi was here, \Nhe would be on Yuán Shào's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.55,0:16:25.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If you send Yúnchǎng to defeat Yuán Shào's army,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.82,0:16:28.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yuán Shào would suspect Liú Bèi and slay him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If Liú Bèi dies, then who will \NYúnchǎng have to follow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, send someone to Xǔdū and get Yúnchǎng immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.61,0:16:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The men of Héběi are known to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.16,0:17:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}To me, they are but a pack of squalid hounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.50,0:17:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}Under that standard, that rider in shining armour wielding the blade-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.10,0:17:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}he is called {\i1}Yán Liáng{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.02,0:17:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}To me, Yan Liang's head is like merchandise to be taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.78,0:17:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They are to not be taken lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.48,0:17:37.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I may lack talent, but I can charge in, seize his head, and present it to you, sire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.79,0:17:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no jests in times of war. \NYúncháng, don't be reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.26,0:17:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound the drums!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.13,0:18:24.32,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo defeated Yán Liáng with Guān Yǔ, \Nand became close allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:30.91,Thinking,NTP,0,0,0,,{\i1}He petitioned Emperor Xiàn of Hàn to promote Guān Yǔ as the 'Precinct Marquis of Hànshòu'.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.99,0:18:33.13,Thinking,NTP,0,0,0,,Forging him a seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.58,0:18:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord, my Lord, vanguard general Yán Liáng has been fallen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.02,0:18:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What! Who could kill Yán Liáng?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.09,0:18:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A warrior with a red face and a long beard! He wielded a glaive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:53.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,His horse just burst through, unstopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.07,0:18:56.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He beheaded Yán Liáng and left!\NOur army suffered a major defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.10,0:18:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.37,0:19:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He is Liú Xuándé's younger brother, Guān Yúnchǎng.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.04,0:19:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.56,0:19:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your younger brother killed my most favored general!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.47,0:19:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be colluding with Cáo Cāo!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.51,0:19:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.02,0:19:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.95,0:19:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait sire! Don't let one-sided words end our alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.48,0:19:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,For our {\i1}alliance{\i0}. Fine, I'll let you speak for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Since my defeat at Xú province, I haven't seen or heard of my brother Yúnchǎng's survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.72,0:19:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many across the world look alike to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.37,0:19:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so how could this man also happen to be Guān Yǔ?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.70,0:19:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, why not confirm this first,\N then make a decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.95,0:19:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see the man who killed Yán Liáng?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.48,0:19:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I almost killed a decent man because of you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.65,0:19:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord, General Yán and I were oath-sworn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.62,0:19:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I must avenge him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.59,0:19:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord, please let me meet with the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.56,0:19:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No one could besides General Wén!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.42,0:20:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you 10,000 men. Cross the Yellow River, hunt down that fiend!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.30,0:20:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sire, you shouldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.00,0:20:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our plan now should be to remain in Yán-City,\N and send a detachment to Guāndù as our next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.27,0:20:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If the situation goes awry when we cross the river, \Nthere is no turning back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.74,0:20:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You burden us with your humdrum. \NAnymore from you will still us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.32,0:20:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch the men. We will leave immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.92,0:20:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.56,0:20:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wén Chǒu is a famed general of Héběi. \NWho will take him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I will go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.92,0:20:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,En garde, Wén Chǒu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.20,0:21:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare fire, quisling!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.35,0:21:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,En garde, knave!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.04,0:21:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guān is a real miracle-worker!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.04,0:21:20.14,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,540,1900,2380)\pos(603.486,342.4)}Zhāng Liáo\NStyled: Wényuǎn
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.56,0:21:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.51,0:21:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.09,0:21:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.90,0:21:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear someone call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.56,0:21:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.93,0:21:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Was someone calling to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.47,0:22:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Liú Bèi! What is your excuse this time!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.64,0:22:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I do wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.59,0:22:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.60,0:22:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You sent your younger brother to kill my best generals!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.20,0:22:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you dare to ask what's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.27,0:22:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him out! Off with his head!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.72,0:22:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Wait! Let me have my final word!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.78,0:22:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Sire! Everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.10,0:22:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Cáo Cāo heeds me with restlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.06,0:22:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Now he's learned of me residing at Sire's side, fearing our alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.52,0:22:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}That's why he has ordered Yúnchǎng to kill the two generals, aimed to enrage Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.74,0:22:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Turning me to be the target for the noble men of Héběi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.46,0:22:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}To twist Sire's own arm to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.82,0:23:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Nobles of Héběi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.22,0:23:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Is there no one who could speak for me to Sire?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.00,0:23:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Why have I been so forsaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.27,0:23:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuándé! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.70,0:23:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuándé is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.16,0:23:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You almost harmed my virtuous reputation!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.94,0:24:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no way of repaying \NYour Lordship's magnanimity!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.24,0:24:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I will send a trusted messenger to meet with Yúnchǎng in secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.51,0:24:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When he learns of my whereabouts, Yúnchǎng will rush through the night join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.56,0:24:21.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We'll assist you, sire, to execute that traitor Cáo, \Nand avenge Yán Liáng and Wén Chǒu!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.26,0:24:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If I acquired Yúnchǎng, he'll be worth more than ten Yán Liángs and Wén Chǒus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.54,0:24:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.16,0:24:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not prepare brush and ink,\Nwrite this message before everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.78,0:24:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guān!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.82,0:24:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.45,0:24:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One of your old acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.39,0:24:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.60,0:24:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.66,0:25:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guān!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.73,0:25:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.32,0:25:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you claim to be my acquaintance?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.56,0:25:08.40,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,540,1900,2380)\pos(612.914,332.667)}Chén Zhèn\NStyled: Xiàoqǐ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.20,0:25:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I am General Yuán Shào's subordinate, {\i1}Chén Zhèn of Nányáng.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.19,0:25:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is Liú Bèi's personal letter. \NGeneral Guān, please read.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.50,0:25:42.80,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}"You and I made oath at the Peach-Garden, sworn to die as brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.20,0:25:46.64,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}Yet now a rift is between our path, how could you forget our promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.47,0:25:55.14,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}But if you wish for fame and fortune, to achieve your triumph, my head is yours for the taking,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.26,0:25:59.24,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}I will not say a word, none could suffice. \NI will await for death.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.92,0:26:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that I don't want to find you,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.77,0:26:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but that I do not know where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.07,0:26:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, how could I betray \Nour oath for wealth and glory?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.62,0:26:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuándé is hoping to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.90,0:26:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do not want to betray your old oath, then you should go see him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.28,0:27:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}Men are born between heaven and earth,\N giving up is not a noble path.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.79,0:27:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}I understood this before coming, and I can't not understand when leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.47,0:27:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}I will write a letter, please sir, \Nif you could, inform my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.18,0:27:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}I will leave Cáo Cāo, and bring my sisters-in-law to reunite with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.49,0:27:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If Cáo Cāo won't let you leave, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.60,0:27:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather accept death. \NHow could I remain here?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.80,0:27:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir should write a reply, to reassure Lord Liú.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.09,0:28:17.45,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}As it's said, \Nthe righteous do not regret, the loyal do not fear death.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.70,0:28:22.96,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}Since youth, I've learned honour and integrity from books,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.93,0:28:27.13,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}from stories of Yáng Jiǎo'āi and Zuǒ Bótáo,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.93,0:28:31.40,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Yáng Jiǎo'āi and Zuǒ Bótáo were close friends who struggled and sacrificed for one another in the Warring States era.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.57,0:28:31.54,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}lessons and principles that moved me so, that I have lived by since.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.71,0:28:36.04,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)} I guarded Xiapi, without grain
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.40,0:28:40.08,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}and without reserves, making my last stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.32,0:28:43.38,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}But with the lives of my sisters-in-laws
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.61,0:28:48.56,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}I couldn't dare to sacrifice myself, betray your trust and my duty,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.00,0:28:53.92,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}thus I had to yield for the time being, \Nuntil our hopeful reunion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.08,0:28:57.90,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}Now that I have received Elder Brother's letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.93,0:29:01.34,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}I shall leave sir Cáo,\N and return with my sisters-in-laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.44,0:29:04.82,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}If I held the slightest sway of heart, may the gods strike me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.94,0:29:08.13,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}I lay my hearts bare, \Nthese feelings that cannot be written.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.27,0:29:11.72,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,440.666)}Soon, I hope, I can be by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.88,0:29:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I know my brother's heart, \NI know all unsaid questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.91,0:29:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If there are complaints, I am willing to bear them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.18,0:29:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Wényuǎn, what is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.88,0:29:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I have heard you received news of sir Xuándé, and came to congratulate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.29,0:30:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Although my lord is still alive, I can't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.47,0:30:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why congratulate?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.71,0:30:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The relationship between you and Xuándé...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.82,0:30:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,how does it compare to ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.92,0:30:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.63,0:30:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuándé and I are both friends, and brothers most of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.57,0:30:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And we are also lord and vassal. \NHow could you compare the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.04,0:30:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Xuándé is at Héběi.\NSir, are you going there?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.45,0:31:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I betray my promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.63,0:31:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Wényuǎn, you must see the Chancellor\Nto convey my will on my behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.97,0:31:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yúnchǎng has decided?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.34,0:31:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A just man's words are to the point, \Nevery sentence flies true.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.95,0:31:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have ever agreed to his terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.52,0:31:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, if not for your promise, how could Yúnchǎng follow us?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.23,0:31:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If so...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.47,0:31:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting him go is a pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.34,0:31:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you force Yúnchǎng to stay, he will resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.78,0:32:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the problem exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.85,0:32:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wényuǎn, you may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.26,0:32:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.69,0:32:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a plan to keep him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.83,0:32:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.90,0:32:38.32,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(364.815,160.8)}'Withdraw'
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.67,0:32:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose Wényuǎn told him my will\N and the Chancellor is avoiding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.20,0:33:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Inform General Zhāng that I have urgent matters to discuss!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.64,0:33:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,General Zhāng is resting, and will not to receive any visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.78,0:33:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask sir to please tell the general. \NTell him Guān Yu wants to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.30,0:33:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I am under specific orders from General Zhāng.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.10,0:33:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guān, you are no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.10,0:33:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.43,0:33:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.83,0:33:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wényuǎn, am I not a guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.42,0:33:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you use sleep \Nas an excuse to reject my visit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.72,0:34:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you won't see me, I will go see the Chancellor again!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.48,0:34:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, sorry for the bother. \NWhy won't the Chancellor see guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.46,0:34:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only a servant within the house. \NI know nothing of the Chancellor's affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.90,0:34:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You know nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.53,0:35:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.32,0:35:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My wish to leave is set, how could I stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.76,0:35:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,General,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.70,0:35:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,General,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.50,0:35:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you checked carefully?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.96,0:35:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As according to your will, \NI wouldn't dare make a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.24,0:35:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.02,0:35:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please, tell me that the Chancellor's gifts...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.11,0:35:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Have them all stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.47,0:36:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not let anyone touch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.08,0:36:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.29,0:36:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Only...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.52,0:36:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.92,0:36:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}This seal is received from the Imperial Court.\NPlease carry it with you, general.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.96,0:37:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}This seal is from the Chancellor. I won't carry it!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.04,0:37:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,General!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.28,0:37:31.46,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Now I have learned of my lord's presence at Yuan Shao's camp-
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.50,0:37:35.06,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}- by my promised allegiance, how can I abandon him?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.28,0:37:38.36,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Even before your generousity, I am still honor-bound.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.46,0:37:42.24,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}Thus I have written this letter to offer my gratitude and farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.40,0:37:47.02,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,453.2)}If there are more debts between us, I shall repay them in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.30,0:37:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Reporting to the Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.55,0:37:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Guān Yǔ has locked away all the gifted gold and silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.92,0:38:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The ten beauties have all\N been housed in a separate room.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.78,0:38:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Marquis' seal of Hànshòu-Precinct has been hung up at the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.98,0:38:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the men Chancellor\N had assigned have been left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.95,0:38:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He only took his own followers and luggage, and left from the North Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.50,0:38:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.47,0:38:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take 3,000 cavalry to go capture \NGuān Yǔ and deliver him to you, Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.80,0:38:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, please give the order!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.95,0:38:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Never forgot his roots, \Nparting with nay a debt or a word. What a true man!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.43,0:38:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You all should follow his example.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.66,0:38:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, you'd let him go just like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.14,0:39:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to your stations!\NDo not speak of this again!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.86,0:39:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Chancellor has treated Guan Yu graciously, \Nyet now he leaves without a word in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.00,0:39:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}His writing is but insolence to your might, and shouldn't be tolerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.14,0:39:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}If he were to join with Yuan Shao, would be like giving wings to a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.88,0:39:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Better to capture and kill him now, and remove a potential threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.14,0:39:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You will {\i1}not.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.32,0:39:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}I've made my promise, I will not break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.56,0:39:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}We all live true to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.26,0:39:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}You will not chase him!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.36,0:39:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Wényuǎn?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.80,0:39:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.32,0:40:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Yúnchǎng has hunged seal and locked the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.14,0:40:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Riches could not sway him, titles could not move him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.14,0:40:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Such men have my utmost respect!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.86,0:40:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}He won't have gone far, I will do him one last favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.18,0:40:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Wényuǎn, have Yúnchǎng halt for a moment to await my escort.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.22,0:40:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Gift him a warrior's cloak and toll for the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.52,0:40:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,459.333)}Let this be our parting memory.
